Let’s talk about my “Giant frog” Dump’s eyes and why they sometimes look different. Dumpy is an Australian whites tree frog and like most frogs she is nocturnal; and because of this her eyes are very good at seeing in the dark; frogs pupils will expand to let in much more light then a humans eye can. Depending on how much light is around her her eyes will adapt by opening and closing the pupil giving the eye a completely different appearance. This is why Dumpy’s eyes may appear different throughout our videos. If you would like to learn more about my “Giant” pet frog tap on the folder at the the bottom of this video. Consider hitting the plus icon; and check out what else I’m up to. We appreciate your support. #giantfrog  #dumpytreefrog  #petfrog  #frogeyes  #learnontiktok

Let’s talk about Dumpy the big frogs house called a Paludarium; we will teach you about her frog enclosure needs / husbandry and all the animals that live in her this fish tank. Helps keep your food warm as your plate! 4. Go for a dry white wine; i.e.; Riesling or Pinot Grigio.   Pasta Sauce (for 2): - 1 garlic clove - 1-2 small chillies - 250g cherry tomatoes* - Splash of white wine - 150g finely diced prawns - 150g fish or chicken stock - Good splash of olive oil  *For peeled skin; score an "x" at the core of the tomato skin and blanch for 10 secs in boiling water; place under call water or ice bath!  Steps to success:  Heat a frying pan until hot; add olive oil and prawns. Cook until they have a nice colour on one side remove immediately and place in a container (you don't want to overcook). Allow the same pan to cool; then add a bit more olive oil and finely diced garlic clove and small chilli(s). Gently heat until fragrant but do not burn (be careful it goes quickly with garlic and chillies). Add cherry tomatoes and stir through until slightly broken and soft. Add a splash of white wine and reduce. Add stock and reduce by 3/4. Set aside and keep warm.   Assembly: - Small handful of parsley finely chopped - 40g parmesan cheese (30g approx for sauce and remainder 10g for garnish) - Salt and Pepper to taste  Steps for success:  Once your pasta is cooked to al dente add directly into the sauce. Add finely chopped parsley and parmesan cheese and stir through. Divide portions between two plates. Garnish with a bit of parsley and parmesan cheese.   Semolina Pasta (for 2): - 125g Semolina Flour  - 1 egg + 1 egg yolk - 1 teaspoon olive oil  - Pinch of sea salt  Process: Combine everything and kneed into a smooth dough. Wrap up and allow to rest for 30 min in the fridge before proceeding to make the pasta sheets. The suggestion here is to go on the lower-end setting so you have thin pasta sheets. You can cut them into strips if you don't have additional pasta attachments. Dust with plenty of flour and cook until al dente.

A Flaky Start: Exhibit B - Croissant & Hot Chocolate. #croissants  #hotchocolate  #pastries  #desserts   Taste 8/10 Visuals 7/10  Hot chocolate recipe (serves 2-4) - 200g chopped dark chocolate - 2 tablespoon of brown sugar - 2 tablespoons of cacao powder - pinch of sea salt - 400g organic milk

I want to be that freaky fantasy that is always on your mind. #desserts  #praline  #parisbrest  #pastries   Taste 8/10  Visuals 5/10  Here we have a classic Paris Brest with Praline Moussaline. I served it with a coffee and tonka ice cream; chocolate sauce; and easy whipped cream. Ingredients and notes below!  Filling - 240g heavy cream  - 150g milk  - 1x vanilla pod - 80g caster sugar - 60g egg yolks - 40g corn starch - 125g white chocolate (to be added into the hot custard) - 250g praline - 150g butter  Choux (makes to large rings): - 125g milk  - 125g water - 125g butter - 6g salt - 8g sugar - 380g flour - 250g eggs (5x approx.)

Episode 21 | Teaching your next date how to cook. #datenight  #ramennoodles  #ramenhacks  #saucy   5-star Fast Food Ramen Recipe! Taste 9/10 Difficulty: Easy to Medium   Briefing: So here we have an easy-peasy date night recipe dish. Super fun and it tastes delicious. Tbh; I think this is one of my favourites amongst the churros and dessert pizza.  Before you begin: Serves 2; so you need 2 noodle packets. I went with Korean noodles for this recipe but you could switch it up as you please. So; if you went for more Japanese ramen noodle packets then switch the Gochujang with miso paste for example.   Garnish Ideas:  - Pork Belly (recipe below) - House-made ramen (check serious eats) - Seaweed - Mozzarella shreds  - Rice cakes  - Soft-boiled egg - Scallions  Ramen Broth for 2 Part 1 - 2 packets of Korean instant ramen broth powder + 600g water - A few slices of spring onions; 4 button mushrooms finely slices; a few slices of fresh ginger; and 4 dried shitake mushrooms (optional) - 16 gelatine bloomed sheets for a silkier mouth feel (optional)  Process: Add together and allow to simmer for 30 minutes. Strain and add bloomed gelatine. Mix until well combined and keep warm. Heat before serving.   Part 2 (per bowl) -	1 egg yolk -	1 tsp Gochujang -	2 tsp kewpie mayo  -	1 tsp sweet soy sauce  -	1 tsp regular soy sauce -	1 tsp olive oil  -	1 tsp sesame oil  Process: Add everything in a bowl and mix. Repeat the process with the second bowl. When all your other garnishes are ready and prepped; add gently half of your hot broth and mix in.   Pork Belly Recipe - 400g pork belly - 1kg  water + 1 chicken stock cube - 330g light soy sauce - 225g sweet soy sauce  - 81g packed brown sugar - 125g oyster sauce - 9 star anise  - 5 black peppercorns - 15 ginger slices  - 2 garlic cloves - 2 cinnamon sticks  - 1 bay leave  - 30g Gochujang (optional)  Process: Add everything to a medium to a large pot. Bring to boil with the pork belly then back to a gentle simmer for 1.5 to 2hrs. Allow to cool slightly then slice to desired thickness. Notes: Use 300g of leftover stock and reduce until it thickens. Use this stock to baste pork belly slices and torch to get a beautiful char/caramelization.

🇵🇭🇯🇵 Seafood Kare Kare 🦀🦐 collab w/ @ケンティー健人/kenty    Decided to put a twist on the iconic savory peanut stew of the Philippines using the fresh and delicious seafood of Japan 😋 This came out absolutely amazing especially when served Nabemono Style (Hotpot). Perfect to share with friends!  INGREDIENTS:  Seafood: - 1 snow crab - 1/4 kg clams - 1/4 kg squid; chopped - 1/4 kg japanese sweet shrimp  Veg: - onions - garlic - ginger - 1/2 banana flower; chopped - French beans - 1 eggplant; sliced  Other ingredients: - toasted rice flour diluted in water - 1 tbsp Annato powder - 2 tbsp bagoong (Filipino shrimp paste) - 1/2 cup peanut butter - 3 cups water - Salt and Pepper to taste  INSTRUCTIONS: - In a pot; add in vegetable oil and 1 tbsp of annato powder. Saute onionsc garlic and ginger until fragrant. Add in Bagoong and fry for 2 more mins. - Add in your banana heart/flower; saute for 4 mins and add in your squid. Add in peanut butter and cover with water. Add in your diluted toasted rice flout and let cook for around 5 mins. Season to taste with salt/pepper/fish sauce. - Add in your seafood and vegatables. cover and let cook for around 5-10mins. Best served with rice and extra bagoong!   #karekare  #pinoyfood  #pinoyeats  #filipinocooking  #pinoycooking  #japanesefood  #japan  #japanesecooking  #seafood  #crab  #shrimp  #foodph  #filipinojapanesecuisine  #foodtok  #cookingasmr  #asmr

🇵🇭🇯🇵 Tuna Sisig  Collab w/ @バヤシ🥑Bayashi    This is a non-traditional Sisig w/ a slight twist using ingredients we had in Japan! It came out really yummy especially since the seafood in Japan is extra fresh 😋 the tuna was not hard at all and very tender when cooked!  Ingredients: - Tuna sashimi portion - Flour; egg; panko - 1 large onion; diced - 5 cloves garlic; sliced - 4 chili peppers; sliced - 1 lime; juiced - 4 pcs chicken liver; seared and chopped - 2 tbsp soy sauce - 2 tbsp rice vinegar - Salt & pepper to taste  Toppings & Garnish: - Japanese mayo - Spring onions; chopped - Egg yolk  #sisig  #pinoyfood  #pinoyeats  #filipinocooking  #pinoycooking  #japanesefood  #japan  #japanesecooking  #tuna  #foodph  #filipinojapanesecuisine  #foodtok  #cookingasmr  #asmr

Mushroom Chicharon w/ Guacamole 🍄🥑  Mushroom chicharon is quite popular here in the Philippines so I decided to make a version paired with Guacamole! Definitely a much healthier alternative and vegan friendly version of this pairing. Great as a snack or food to share 🤩  Mushroom Chicharon: - Oyster mushrooms - 1/2 Tapioca Flour  - 1/2 All purpose flour - Salt & Pepper to taste - Chipotle seasoning (any powder of your choice)  𝗚𝘂𝗮𝗰𝗮𝗺𝗼𝗹𝗲: - 2 Avocados  - 2 Tomatoes (diced) - 2 Jalapenos (to taste if you want it less spicy)  - 1/2 Red Onion (diced) - 1/4 cup Cilantro (chopped) - Juice of 1 large lime (or to taste) - Salt to taste  Instructions: - Wash mushrooms in ice cold water and squeeze to drain. You may also use a salad spinner to get rid of extra moisture. - Combine equal parts flour and tapioca starch along with any seasonings like garlic powder/paprika.  - Coat mushrooms in flour mixture and deep fry at 165 for around 5 mins. Strain from oil and deep fry again at a higher temp (180C) for around 30secs-1min or until golden brown. - Season with your powdered seasoning of choice (here I used chipotle seasoning) -  To make guacamole; just combine the listed ingredients and mash them to your desired consistency (smooth/chunky)  #chicharron  #guacamole  #cookingasmr  #asmr  #mexicanfood  #filipinofood

Today President Biden said “My warning to the Ayatollah was that if they continued to move against our troops we will respond and he should be prepared.” The Marine Corps top general issued a warning yesterday saying “For those that are in the area; if that Marine Expeditionary Unit has to go in; if you target them; someone else will raise your children.” Yesterday the US delivered a stark warning at the UN to Iran and now The White House says they’re sending even MORE forces to the Middle East. US officials say they have intelligence that Iran is encouraging its terror groups to ramp up attacks on the United States according to Reuters. With one U.S. official saying “there are red lights flashing everywhere.”

US Moves Carrier Closer To Iran #usa  #israel    The USS Eisenhower; the 2nd aircraft carrier the US sent to Israel; will now move to the Persian Gulf according to the Pentagon. This puts the US closer to its bases in the region and closer to Iran. The Guardian is reporting that ISIS and Al-Qaeda are calling on their followers to attack Israel and the US. In other parts of the world: The Philippines has accused China of intentionally colliding with their ships on a resupply mission. The US has sided with the Philippines and once again reaffirmed their mutual defense treaty. In an exclusive; Rolling Stone is reporting that Trump is planning on pulling the United States out of NATO if he wins the Presidency again. Russia began an offensive in the past two weeks and it’s gone about as well as the initial invasion did. Only advancing a few hundred meters. Ukraine says Russia has lost over 400 vehicles and 6;000 soldiers. How’s the expression go? If at first you don’t succeed; try; try again.

US Fears Region-Wide War #usa  #israel    The US fears a widening region-wide war; US officials tell Axios. With the Pentagon now putting even more troops on “prepare to deploy orders” This comes as the US has sent two aircraft carriers to the region; surged aircraft to its bases in the Middle East; and added more air defense systems and all weekend; US bases all over the region were attacked by terror groups. The rhetoric coming out of Israel and Iran has been white hot; with the BBC reporting that Iran warned Israel that if they don’t stop striking Gaza - the region will spiral out of control. Israel and Hezbollah are continuing to exchange fire with each other on the northern border. With the New York Times reporting that the United States has told Israel to not conduct a preemptive strike on Hezbollah. With the outlet also saying the US believes that Israel would struggle in a two front war; and that such a war would drag both them and Iran into it.

US Forces Under Assault Across Middle East #usa  #israel    The United States has issued a very rare worldwide caution travel alert due to the risk of terror attacks; protests; and violent actions against Americans. Reuters reports that US officials say that a Hezebollah linked terror group used drones to attack a US Military base in Syria today causing minor injuries. Meanwhile the Pentagon says a US Navy warship operating in the Northern Red Sea today intercepted 3 cruise missiles and several drones that were fired from the Houthi militant group in Yemen. The Pentagon says the missiles were potentially headed towards Israel which is why they intercepted them; but that they can’t currently confirm that Israel was the target. Channel 13 in Israel is reporting that Israel believes that the missiles were launched at them. And just now Reuters is reporting that two security sources tell them that yet another US base in Iraq has been hit with drones and missiles; this is reportedly the 5th attack on US forces in Iraq and Syria in the past 36 hours. The US has also ordered Americans to leave Lebanon as soon as possible and has changed its travel advisory to “Do Not Travel”.

Arancini with Arrabbiata sauce made using @Napolina ’s finest chopped tomatoes #AD  #NotSoHumbleIngredients   Recipe   Arrabbiata Sauce:   1 onion 5 cloves garlic  1/2 tsp chilli flakes  1 tbsp Napolina tomato puree  2 tins Napolina chopped tomaotoes  6 basil leaves   Arancini:   1 onion  2 cups Arborio rice  4 cups chicken (or vegetable) stock  25g butter  1/2 cup parmesan  1 mozzarella ball  2 eggs  breadcrumbs  oil for frying   For the Arrabbiata sauce; begin with finely chopping the onion (plus an extra one for the Arancini) and garlic.  Get a pan on a medium heat and add two tbsp of olive oil. Add the chilli flakes and cook for 1-2 minutes. Add the onions and sweat down for a further 2-3 minutes. Add the garlic; stir and then squeeze in the tomato paste. Stir well.  Add the tin tomatoes; with a little water and the basil leaves. Give it one final stir and leave to simmer on low for 30 minutes.  For the Arancini; add two tbsp of olive oil to a sauce pan on medium - high heat and add the onions. Sweat down for a couple of minutes and then add the rice. Mix well and cook for 1 minute. Then add the stock. Cover and leave to simmer following package instructions (roughly 10-12 minutes).  Once the rice is cooked add the butter and parmesan; stir through and remove from the heat.  Spread the rice out over a baking tray and leave to fully cool.  Slice the Mozzarella into cubes.  Using wet hands grab a small handful of the rice. Place the mozzarella in the middle and roll into golf ball size balls.  Ideally you should let them set in the fridge for at least two hours (but if you can't wait then march on).  Crack two eggs into a bowl and whisk well.  Add the breadcrumbs (season to your preference) to a plate.  Drop the Arancini into the eggs and then straight into the bread crumbs. Make sure they are evenly coated and shake off the excess.  In a deep sauce pan heat 2 1/2 inches of oil (canola; sunflower etc) and heat to 180c/350f.  Carefully drop the Arancini into the oil. Move them every so often so they don't stick to the bottom and burn.  Once a deep golden brown colour; remove and place onto paper towel. Season with a little salt.  Let them rest for a couple of minutes and then serve with the Arrabbiata sauce on the side.  Enjoy!

Irmãos; falo dessa palavra com urgência. É muito triste ver pessoas crentes exibindo seus bens materiais e sua aparência física a todo o custo; pondo sua esperança e redenção nas coisas terrenas. Uma coisa é fato: a boca fala do que o coração está cheio. E o meu coração está farto de futilidades; talvez por um momento eu tenha deixado de pregar o evangelho com fervor aqui em meu perfil; mas eu cansei de correr atrás do vento; cansei de não ser a diferença em meio a uma geração perversa e blasfemadora; cansei de me parecer com meninas ímpias aqui na internet. A partir de agora quero que meu perfil aponte para um único Deus: Jesus Cristo; e não para mim mesma; um ídolo que ergui meu próprio coração.  A hora é chegada! Maranata; ora vem Senhor Jesus.

Muchas veces padecemos de un cansancio excesivo; se nos cruzan sensaciones de tristeza y pensamientos oscuros.  Esta es una técnica ancestral para alejar las malas vibras.  Generalmente culpamos al exterior por sentirnos cansados y agotados; pero muchas veces esto tiene que ver con algo que hacemos nosotros mismos. Tener pensamientos negativos baja nuestra vibración y es así que las energías densas del ambiente pueden ingresar.  ¡Somos el resultado de nuestros pensamientos y responsables de lo que intercambiamos con el entorno!  También puede haber episodios recurrentes de "mala suerte". Sabés a que me refiero; ¿verdad? A todos nos pasó o nos pasa de vez en cuando.  Acá estoy facilitándote esta forma de descargarte de todo lo malo y devolver esas energías.  No importa cual sea tu creencia; es necesaria una protección; siempre; el solo hecho de salir a la calle nos contamina de las energías que están en el aire; un viaje en subte lleno de gente enojada; una consulta a en un hospital "cargado" de tristeza; pueden ya bajarte la vibración del cuerpo energético.  Siempre estoy buscando brindarte recomendaciones fáciles así las puedas implementar y esta no es la excepción!.   Te invito también a sumarte a mi abrecaminos de Noviembre!. “EL RITUAL FULMINANTE de LIBERACIÓN; PURIFICACIÓN y PROTECCIÓN CONTRA TODO MAL”.  Para alejar todo lo malo que estés atravesando; atrayendo positivismo como así también buenas energías para estos días venideros donde ya literalmente debemos comenzar a prepáranos para navidad 🎄.
